# Epic Completion Evaluation Projection

## Purpose

This projection defines how implemented repository reality should be certified against an epic, its milestone specifications, and the Core North-Star.

It exists to support:

- epic completion certification
- milestone completion certification
- acceptance criteria evaluation
- strategic success evaluation
- capability realization assessment
- architectural preservation assessment
- constraint preservation assessment
- evidence quality assessment
- strategic drift classification
- strategic learning extraction
- closure recommendation

It is a projection of the Core North-Star, not an epic, milestone spec, repository audit, implementation summary, roadmap update, or completion report.

## Authority Boundary

- The Core North-Star remains the source of authority.
- This projection is a task-specific certification view of the Core North-Star.
- This projection defines how EvaluateEpicCompletionAndDrift should judge completion and drift.
- This projection does not include `.agents/epic.md`.
- This projection does not include `.agents/milestones/*.md`.
- This projection does not include repository state.
- This projection does not evaluate actual implementation.
- This projection does not produce completion findings.
- This projection does not produce drift findings.
- This projection does not update roadmap completion context.
- This projection does not modify roadmap, epic, milestone specs, code, or operational context.

