## Downstream Use Instructions

When this projection is used by EvaluateEpicCompletionAndDrift:

- Treat this projection as the certification frame.
- Treat `.agents/epic.md` as intended epic outcome.
- Treat `.agents/milestones/*.md` as intended milestone outcomes.
- Treat the repository as authoritative evidence of implemented reality.
- Distinguish implementation from capability realization.
- Distinguish acceptance satisfaction from strategic success.
- Evaluate every epic acceptance criterion individually.
- Evaluate every milestone individually.
- Evaluate every milestone acceptance criterion individually.
- Certify milestone completion before epic completion.
- Evaluate drift independently from completion.
- Classify positive and negative drift when evidence supports them.
- Do not certify completion without repository evidence.
- Do not treat handoff or execution history as completion evidence unless corroborated.
- Extract strategic learning for downstream roadmap completion context update.
- Do not update roadmap completion context.
- Do not modify the roadmap.
- Do not modify epic or milestone specs.
- Do not create implementation tasks.
- Preserve canonical vocabulary.

