Before finalizing, verify:

- The projection contains certification semantics only.
- No epic content is included.
- No milestone spec content is included.
- No repository state is included.
- No completion findings are produced.
- No drift findings are produced.
- Every retained statement helps certify completion or classify drift.
- Every major retained statement traces to the Core North-Star or is clearly marked projection-local.
- Certification layer semantics are explicit.
- Capability certification rules are explicit.
- Milestone certification rules are explicit.
- Epic certification rules are explicit.
- Acceptance semantics are explicit.
- Strategic success semantics are explicit.
- Evidence quality standards are explicit.
- Drift interpretation rules are explicit.
- Certification blockers are explicit.
- Strategic learning extraction rules are explicit.
- Closure recommendation semantics are explicit.
- Traceability requirements are explicit.
- Canonical vocabulary is preserved.
- Excluded operational, implementation, roadmap, preparation, realignment, reimagination, planning, and execution details are not present.
- The projection is compact enough to be passed into EvaluateEpicCompletionAndDrift.